<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-02T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-02T03:00:00-05:00" n="551" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2909: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-02T17:00:00+09:00"><hi rend="italic">August 2,
                                            1920—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 2—9:20
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>389. Your 282, July 23, 5 p.m. Corrections having arrived I have
                                to-day presented proclamation to Foreign Office and asked for an
                                early reply.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>